│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Wait, let me reconsider the range. If both operands are non-negative (0-127), then the result is 1-127.                                                                               │
│ If both operands are negative (128-255), then as signed values they are -128 to -1.                                                                                                   │
│ When we do `sub nsw` on two negative numbers where the first is "greater" (less negative), the result is positive.                                                                    │
